reports/codex_tool_reports/dec_v61_054_p1_t1_arc_review.log:6668:4. ADR-001 plane contract compliance (.importlinter + ADR §2.1): The arc classifies src.metrics as Evaluation. SpectralMetric avoids importing src.cylinder_strouhal_fft (Execution) and reads scalars from key_quantities instead. But semantic_delegate string src.cylinder_strouhal_fft is preserved in delegate_to_module class attr. Is this hybrid approach defensible or does it indicate ADR-001 misclassified cylinder_strouhal_fft? Run: grep -rn cylinder_strouhal_fft src/metrics/ — should return only string references, no actual imports.
reports/codex_tool_reports/dec_v61_054_p1_t1_arc_review.log:6670:5. Tolerance-policy dispatch bug in registry.evaluate_all (src/metrics/registry.py L105-108): per_metric_tol = tolerance_policy.get(name, tolerance_policy) — falls back to WHOLE policy dict when no per-name entry. If the outer policy has a top-level tolerance key, every metric lacking a per-name entry gets the same override. Is this the intended semantic or a latent bug? test_tolerance_policy_without_tolerance_key_is_ignored covers one side but not the cross-pollination case.
