commit 0450df636c099d3484ae66de0b8f6c0d7a5a4028
Author: claude-opus47-app <claude-opus47-app@anthropic.com>
Date:   Sat Apr 25 01:57:25 2026 +0800

    feat(metrics): P1-T3 CaseProfile.tolerance_policy schema + loader
    
    Adds per-observable tolerance overrides to CaseProfile v1 schema
    (additive to G-6 risk_flags). Loader returns shape consumable by
    MetricsRegistry.evaluate_all per METRICS_AND_TRUST_GATES §4 dispatch
    and consistent with DEC-V61-054 R1 finding #2 fix (per-name-only
    dispatch, no top-level fallback).
    
    Schema (YAML, additive block in .planning/case_profiles/<case_id>.yaml):
    
        tolerance_policy:
          <observable_name>:
            tolerance: <float>    # relative, 0..1 (e.g. 0.05 = 5%)
          <observable_name>:
            tolerance: <float>
          ...
    
    Loader contract (src/metrics/case_profile_loader.py):
    - load_case_profile(case_id) → full CaseProfile dict or None
    - load_tolerance_policy(case_id) → dict in evaluate_all shape
    - Absent file / empty file / absent tolerance_policy → {} (falls
      through to observable_def.tolerance downstream)
    - Explicit `tolerance: null` → passes through (residual metrics use
      attestor verdicts, not gold deviation)
    - Raises CaseProfileError on: malformed YAML, tolerance_policy not
      dict, per-observable entry not dict, tolerance non-numeric,
      tolerance is NaN, tolerance is bool (Python treats bool as int —
      explicit guard prevents `tolerance: true` silent acceptance)
    
    Plane: Evaluation. Reads YAML via file I/O (not module import) —
    ADR-001 plane contracts govern import graph only. Resolves
    .planning/case_profiles/ via repo-root walk from module __file__
    (tests override via case_profiles_dir kwarg).
    
    Concrete examples landed in 2 case profiles (out of 10):
    - lid_driven_cavity: u_centerline/v_centerline 5%, primary_vortex_
      location 3% (tighter for location observables · DEC-V61-050)
    - circular_cylinder_wake: strouhal_number 25% (10s-endTime precision-
      limited per DEC-V61-053 R4), cd_mean 5%, cl_rms 30%,
      u_mean_centerline 10%
    
    Remaining 8 case profiles can be backfilled incrementally as each case
    gets its first multi-observable DEC; loader returning {} for absent
    tolerance_policy keeps the fall-through semantics working everywhere.
    
    Tests: 16 new (tests/test_metrics/test_case_profile_loader.py):
    - 4 absence paths (missing file, empty file, no tolerance_policy key,
      missing case_id via case_profiles_dir override)
    - 2 happy paths (well-formed policy, defensive copy)
    - 6 schema-violation paths (malformed YAML, wrong dict nesting, wrong
      types including bool/str/NaN)
    - 1 null-tolerance pass-through (residual metrics)
    - 2 real-repo case profile loads (LDC + cylinder)
    - 1 end-to-end MetricsRegistry.evaluate_all dispatch verifying named
      metric gets override + unnamed metric falls through to observable_def
    
    Full suite: 651 passed (up from 635, +16), 1 skipped. 4 import contracts KEPT.
    
    Refs: PIVOT_CHARTER §7 P1, METRICS_AND_TRUST_GATES §4 tolerance-
    policy dispatch, VCP v1.0 §8.2 accepting clause, DEC-V61-054 R1
    finding #2 (per-name-only semantics), G-6 CaseProfile schema v1.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

